4 (2) As used in this section, the following definitions apply:
5 (a) "Coal and ore haulers" means nonhighway vehicles that exceed 18,000 pounds an axle and
6 that are primarily designed and used to transport coal, ore, or other earthen material in a mining or quarrying
7 environment.
8 (b) "Commercial establishment" includes any hotel, motel, office, petroleum marketing station, or
9 service, wholesale, retail, or food-handling business.
10 (C) (I) "COST" MEANS THE PURCHASE PRICE OF THE PERSONAL PROPERTY, INCLUDING ALL DIRECT AND
11 INDIRECT EXPENSES ASSOCIATED WITH PLACING THE PERSONAL PROPERTY INTO USE.
12 (II) THE TERM DOES NOT INCLUDE AN ALLOCATED PURCHASE PRICE.
13 (c)(D) "Flow lines and gathering lines" means pipelines used to transport all or part of the oil or gas
14 production from an oil or gas well to an interconnection with a common carrier pipeline as defined in 69-13-101
15 or a rate-regulated natural gas transmission or oil transmission pipeline regulated by the public service
16 commission or the federal energy regulatory commission.
17 (d)(E) "Governing body" means the governing body of the county where the class eight property is
18 located.
19 (F) "INDIVIDUAL PIECE OF PERSONAL PROPERTY" MEANS A DISTINCT AND SEPARATE ITEM OF PERSONAL
20 PROPERTY THAT IS NOT PHYSICALLY CONNECTED AS A COMPONENT PART OF A LARGER, INTEGRATED OPERATING
21 SYSTEM OR UNIT, EVEN IF THE PHYSICALLY CONNECTED ITEM OF PERSONAL PROPERTY HAS A COST OF LESS THAN $500.
22 (e)(G) "Manufacturing machinery, fixtures, and equipment" means all property used in the
23 manufacturing process, whether permanently or temporarily in place, to transform raw or finished materials into
24 something possessing a new nature or name and adopted to a new use. The term includes but is not limited to
25 refinery property.
26 (H) "PHYSICALLY CONNECTED" MEANS PERSONAL PROPERTY THAT:
27 (I) IS PERMANENTLY AFFIXED THROUGH MECHANICAL FASTENING, WELDING, OR CHEMICAL BONDING
28 DESIGNED TO REMAIN INTACT DURING NORMAL OPERATION;
