1 (II) SERVES AN ESSENTIAL OPERATIONAL FUNCTION WITHIN AN INTEGRATED MECHANICAL, ELECTRICAL, OR
2 INDUSTRIAL SYSTEM; AND
3 (III) CANNOT BE REMOVED OR REPLACED WITHOUT DAMAGE TO ITSELF OR THE LARGER UNIT OR WITHOUT
4 CAUSING TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT IMPAIRMENT OF THE LARGER UNIT'S FUNCTIONALITY.
5 (3) Except as provided in 15-24-1402 and this section, class eight property is taxed at:
6 (a) for the first $6 million of taxable market value in excess of the exemption amount in subsection
7 (4), 1.5%; and
8 (b) for all taxable market value in excess of $6 million, 3%.
9 (4) (a) (I) Except as provided in subsection (4)(b) AND (4)(C), the first $1 3 $1.5 million of market
10 value of class eight property of a person or business entity is exempt from taxation.
11 (II) WHEN CALCULATING THE MARKET VALUE SUBJECT TO THE EXEMPTION IN SUBSECTION (4)(A)(I), A
12 PROPERTY OWNER IS NOT REQUIRED TO INCLUDE PERSONAL PROPERTY DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (4)(C) WITH A COST
13 OF $500 OR LESS.
14 (III) THE EXEMPTION AMOUNT IN SUBSECTION (4)(A)(I) MUST BE ADJUSTED ANNUALLY BY MULTIPLYING THE
15 EXEMPTION AMOUNT BY AN INFLATION FACTOR, WHICH IS DETERMINED BY DIVIDING THE CONSUMER PRICE INDEX FOR
16 JUNE OF THE PRIOR YEAR BY THE CONSUMER PRICE INDEX FOR JUNE OF THE CURRENT YEAR, ROUNDED TO THE
17 NEAREST $1,000. IF THE INFLATION ADJUSTMENT RESULTS IN A DECREASE IN THE EXEMPTION AMOUNT FROM THE
18 PREVIOUS YEAR, THE EXEMPTION AMOUNT MUST REMAIN THE SAME FOR THAT YEAR.
19 (b) Subject to subsection (6), manufacturing machinery, fixtures, and equipment installed and
20 placed in service after December 31, 2022, are exempt or partially exempt from taxation for a period of 5 years
21 starting from the later of the date they were placed in service or October 1, 2023, after which the exemption
22 amount allowed under subsection (6)(d) is phased out at a rate of 20% of the amount allowed by the governing
23 body a year, with the property being assessed at 100% of its taxable value after a 10-year period. An entity that
24 claims a tax exemption under this subsection (4)(b) shall maintain adequate books and records demonstrating
25 the investment the owner made when installing and placing the property into service in the state. The property
26 owners shall make the records available to the department for inspection on request.
27 (C) AN INDIVIDUAL PIECE OF PERSONAL PROPERTY WITH A COST OF LESS THAN $500 IS EXEMPT FROM
28 PROPERTY TAXATION.
